
Business Requirements Document (BRD)

1. Business Objectives

Provide a fast and accessible bike-booking service for urban commuters.

Reduce wait times by auto-matching users with nearby vendors/riders.

Create a transparent fare estimation and secure payment process.

Improve vendor operational efficiency via real-time booking allocation.

Enable the admin team to monitor operations, vendor performance & service quality.

2. Stakeholders

Stakeholder	      Role

End Users	        Book bikes for quick travel
Vendors           Provide bikes and fulfill bookings
(Bike Owners or Captains)	
Admin Team	      Manage platform, vendors, payments, compliance
Tech Team	        Develop & maintain the system
Customer          Handle user issues and escalations
SUPPORT
Payment         	Enables secure transactions
GATEWAY PROVIDER 

3. Current Pain Points

Difficulty in finding affordable short-distance transport quickly.

Manual bike rental processes causing delays and poor user experience.

No real-time system to match nearby bikes with customers.

Vendors lack a unified platform for tracking earnings & fleet usage.

Admins struggle with manual vendor onboarding and dispute management.

4. Proposed Solution

A mobile/web app that:

Allows users to instantly book a nearby bike.

Calculates fare automatically based on distance/time.

Lets vendors approve/auto-accept bookings.

Tracks rides in real-time via GPS.

Integrates digital payments.

Provides dashboards for admin & vendors.

5. Scope

User app for booking bikes

Vendor app/portal for managing rides

Admin dashboard for platform monitoring

Real-time GPS mapping & ETA estimation

Push/email notifications

Basic analytics reports
